summary:
Ok, quick and awful post about Arya in this episode. Im sure someone else has written this better but I haven't seen it.
So it...
body:
Ok, quick and awful post about Arya in this episode. Im sure someone else has written this better but I haven’t seen it.

So it really makes sense that Arya killed the Night King, especially if you consider the Night King = Death. After Arya hits her head she regresses back to Arya at the beginning of the books/show. She’s in Winterfell but it more represents the unfamiliar King’s Landing, where she’s running defense less (essentially). she’s running away from the wights or lannister soldiers until she comes across Berric/Yoren who rescues her and the Hound grabs her she picks up a weapon. She watches Berric die who also represents her father and Yoren and is now left solely with the hound. They escape where they meet the red lady/jaquen, she has her brief training and goes to kill the Night King

summary: Alright people we don't have to insult Jon because he didn't kill the Night King, we don't have to say that Jon was useless in...
body:
Alright people we don’t have to insult Jon because he didn’t kill the Night King, we don’t have to say that Jon was useless in the battle or that Arya is a better character because she killed the Night King. Jon has been fighting the war against the Night King for a long time at this point and in the battle he took out many by riding Danys dragon (I can’t spell the name sorry) and when he got on the ground he tried his best to get to the Night King. Don’t undermine Jon because he didn’t kill the Night King because Jon has faced the white walkers for a long time and doesn’t deserve any of that bullshit

Not to mention Jon is a cute special boy that deserves the world
